summary:
Raxus 

Raxus was a lush world in the Outer Rim Territories' Tion Hegemony that served as the capital planet of the Confederacy...
caption:
Raxus

Raxus was a lush world in the Outer Rim Territories’ Tion Hegemony that served as the capital planet of the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. Renowned for its beauty, Raxus had a temperate climate and was covered with oceans and landmasses. Since the Separatist Senate was headquartered within its capital city of Raxulon, Raxus became home to a number of Confederate senators, including Mina Bonteri of Onderon. Other major Raxian cities included Tamwith Bay, which was located a considerable distance from Raxulon.

summary: People forget Fringe was based on exploring the moral and ethical dilemmas associated with unregulated experimentation on humans...
body:
People forget Fringe was based on exploring the moral and ethical dilemmas associated with unregulated experimentation on humans especially children. 

 That it was mostly based on the question of what would happen to civilization once we start to access and utilize more of our brain rather than the minuscule percentage we do now? 

 It just turned to this massive love story that took over the show because of the undeniable chemistry between Olivia and Peter.

Once in a while, when I miss quality programming, I like to remind myself that is why I had started watching Fringe.  

Before Fringe, it was Star Trek the Next Generation.  Two very rare shows that included scientific theory applications and pseudo science in every episode, wrapping it in some sort of plot. Star Trek writing consultants were actual NASA engineers. Their futurist vessels were aptly named after them. After each episode, the engineering lounge would be buzzing the next day. Haha, the good old days!

I miss that!  I miss having my brain challenged, and my interest piqued.  Not only that, I miss the optimistic outlook real scientists have for the future of this world, regardless of the massive effort we need to undertake as a culture and governments.  Of course it was the political era of Ralph Nader and Green conservationists, not of this regression-ist political-conservative retardation. 

Nonetheless, freedom and justice will triumph. 

If you have not noticed, the number one theme in the film industry has been advocating for the Resistance, for fighting, for us not to give up under dictator rule! 

Live long and prosper!
